TDD (Test-Driven Development)
Goal

Write tests before implementing features to ensure the system is reliable and maintainable.

Phase 1: Machine Learning Tests

Test ID	Test Case	Expected Result
ML-01	Load dataset	Dataset loads successfully
ML-02	Data preprocessing	Clean dataset generated
ML-03	Feature encoding	Features encoded correctly
ML-04	Train model	Model trained successfully
ML-05	Evaluate model	Performance metrics generated
ML-06	Save model	model.joblib file created


Phase 2: Backend Tests

Authentication
Test ID	Test Case	Expected Result
AUTH-01	Register user	User registered successfully
AUTH-02	Duplicate registration	Error returned
AUTH-03	Valid login	Login successful
AUTH-04	Invalid login	Authentication fails
Prediction API
Test ID	Test Case	Expected Result
PRED-01	Load ML model	Model loads successfully
PRED-02	Valid loan details	Prediction returned
PRED-03	Invalid input	Validation error
PRED-04	Prediction response	Status code 200
Database
Test ID	Test Case	Expected Result
DB-01	Save user details	Record stored successfully
DB-02	Save loan application	Record stored successfully
DB-03	Save prediction result	Record stored successfully
DB-04	Retrieve prediction history	Data returned correctly
Phase 3: Frontend Tests
Test ID	Test Case	Expected Result
UI-01	Login page	Loads successfully
UI-02	Registration page	Loads successfully
UI-03	Loan form validation	Invalid inputs show errors
UI-04	Submit loan application	API called successfully
UI-05	Display prediction	Prediction shown correctly
UI-06	Responsive UI	Works on different screen sizes
Integration Tests
Test ID	Test Case	Expected Result
INT-01	Frontend ↔ Backend	Data exchanged successfully
INT-02	Backend ↔ ML Model	Prediction generated correctly
INT-03	Backend ↔ Supabase	Data stored successfully
INT-04	End-to-end workflow	Complete prediction flow works
